<dec f='llvm/polly/include/polly/ScopInfo.h' l='2283' type='bool polly::Scop::trackAssumption(polly::AssumptionKind Kind, isl::set Set, llvm::DebugLoc Loc, polly::AssumptionSign Sign, llvm::BasicBlock * BB)'/>
<doc f='llvm/polly/include/polly/ScopInfo.h' l='2269'>/// Track and report an assumption.
  ///
  /// Use &apos;clang -Rpass-analysis=polly-scops&apos; or &apos;opt
  /// -pass-remarks-analysis=polly-scops&apos; to output the assumptions.
  ///
  /// @param Kind The assumption kind describing the underlying cause.
  /// @param Set  The relations between parameters that are assumed to hold.
  /// @param Loc  The location in the source that caused this assumption.
  /// @param Sign Enum to indicate if the assumptions in @p Set are positive
  ///             (needed/assumptions) or negative (invalid/restrictions).
  /// @param BB   The block in which this assumption was taken. Used to
  ///             calculate hotness when emitting remark.
  ///
  /// @returns True if the assumption is not trivial.</doc>
